The h5 file is more stable in data IO compared to loom file (data from Scanpy to Seurat and SingleCellExperiment)¶

The h5 file unified structure design and data IO method, which is more stable in data IO compared to loom file. Even with cross-platform data IO, h5 has fidelity to categorical (factor) data.

In [1]:

library(SeuratDisk)

Checking whether Seurat read the loom file¶

Unfortunately, Loom file saved by Scanpy is not read very well in Seurat. It is reason probably that the method of handling loom file is different between Scanpy and SeuratDisk

Reading the loom file by calling LoadLoom in SeuratDisk¶

Checking whether SinglecellExperiment read the loom file¶

Unfortunately, Loom file saved by Scanpy is not read very well in LoomExperiment. It is reason probably that the method of handling loom file is different between Scanpy and LoomExperiment. The LoomExperiment converts loom file to the SingleCellExperiment object mainly.
